Package nz.co.jedsimson.lgp.core.program.instructions

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Arity
    The arity of an operation, specifying how many arguments it can take.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BinaryOperation<T>
    An operation that has an arity of two (i.e. its function takes 2 arguments).
    Instruction<TData>
    An instruction in a class Program.
    InstructionGenerator<TProgram,TOutput extends Output<TProgram>,TTarget extends Target<? extends TProgram>>
    A generator of instructions in an LGP system.
    Operation<TData>
    A primitive that encapsulates the action of executing a function on a set of arguments.
    OperationKt  
    UnaryOperation<T>
    An operation that has an arity of one (i.e. its function takes 1 argument).
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    BaseArity
    A base arity implementation that provides arity for instructions with one or two arguments.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ArityException
    Thrown when the interface Arity of an class Operation does not match the number of lgp.core.evolution.registers.Arguments given to it.
